data.enText: to state officially that sth is no longer legally valid

data.chText: 他们的婚姻仅过半年就宣告取消。
data.enText: Their marriage was annulled after just six months.

simple_means.memory_skill: an 表加强 + nul〔= null没有，无〕→ 变没有 → 取消

example: He revoked the ban on smoking

value.def: If an election or a contract is annulled, it is declared invalid, so that legally it is considered never to have existed.

example.ex: Opposition party leaders are now pressing for the entire election to be annulled...
example.tran: 反对党领导人现正强烈要求宣告这次选举无效。

example.ex: The marriage was annulled last month.
example.tran: 上个月这桩婚姻被宣告无效。

value.tran: 废除，取消（合同等）；宣告（选举等）无效
